column4: Here is my time-lapse video of the path of the Sun on the Winter Solstice (12/21/22) from Fairbanks, Alaska. Approximately 3h 12m compressed to 2 minutes. It was so interesting to be at that latitude on the winter solstice.

column14: My focus is preparing folks for the 2024 total solar eclipse, But I took time out to visit Fairbanks, Alaska for the winter solstice. I've always wanted to capture a time-lapse of the Sun rising and setting and only getting 2°above the horizon. The arc spans about 44°. Luckily, I had clear weather.
